        "description": {
            "value": "<p>This surprisingly weighty, though well-balanced, wooden buckler (Hardness 13, HP 104, and BT 52) is emblazoned with the image of a sapling. The sapling withers as the shield takes damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> envision</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The buckler expands, with the sapling image growing into a mighty oak tree. The buckler becomes a tower shield, gaining the corresponding AC bonus, Speed penalty, and ability to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Take Cover]. It keeps the same Hit Points and Broken Threshold, but its Hardness and Bulk increase by 2 in this form. The shield remains in this form until you Activate it again to revert it to a buckler.</p>"
